body:
r? @pcwalton

(rust_highfive has picked a reviewer for you, use r? to override)
With some help on IRC, I got part of the way handling projection types (54e183f).  Still doesn't work completely correctly, though; not sure what's missing.
:umbrella: The latest upstream changes (presumably #26575) made this pull request unmergeable. Please resolve the merge conflicts.
Rebased, and updated with some handling for late-bound lifetimes.  Ready to be reviewed, I think?
:umbrella: The latest upstream changes (presumably #26694) made this pull request unmergeable. Please resolve the merge conflicts.

Updated to address review comments.

Function pointers are now checked.  Tuples are now disallowed.  Zero-size structs are now disallowed.  `is_repr_nullable_ptr` is still a separate function; unifying it with the trans enum handling is going to be a big task.
Any chance fixes (or tests, if these commits already fix them) for #20098 and #19834 could slip in? :-)
This already fixes and tests #20098 (Box was affected by the same issue as String).  #19834 is essentially orthogonal; I don't want to make too many changes at once.

> Pulling the whole algorithm out of trans into librustc is rather complicated... I can do it, but I think I'll submit it as a separate PR (it's a few hundred lines of code).

Seems reasonable

Actually, on second thought, I'd like to hold off on merging this for now until we at least get a crater run. The recent experience with the `missing_docs` lint has shown us that this sort of update to a lint can cause widespread breakage. I think this could easily go in if https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/1193 were implemented, but for now we should evaluate the impact ahead of time.

I'll start a crater run right now.
:umbrella: The latest upstream changes (presumably #26683) made this pull request unmergeable. Please resolve the merge conflicts.
Ah right crater needs to bootstrap at least to run. @eefriedman can you fix the bootstrap issue and re-ping me? I'll kick off the rest of the crater builds at that point.
Ok! new crater builds are now running

Added some Windows-specific build fixes in `src/libstd/sys/windows/stack_overflow.rs` and `src/libstd/rt/unwind/gcc.rs`.  `improper_ctypes` caught a couple missing `[repr(C)]` annotations.

Hopefully it passes tests this time around.
